# Memory Bank
At the start of EVERY task, read ALL files in memory-bank/ before doing anything.
After completing significant work, update the relevant memory-bank/ files.
Before using /newtask, always update memory-bank/activeContext.md and memory-bank/progress.md first.
Use /newtask when the conversation exceeds ~15 messages.

# Thinking
For non-trivial tasks, use sequential-thinking MCP to plan before acting.
Break the problem into steps, state them clearly, then execute one at a time.

# Domain Rules
- Clinical/psychological domain — handle all patient data conservatively
- Never log, print, or hardcode raw patient data or PII
- Psychological risk signals (suicidal ideation, self-harm) must never be trivialized in code, comments, or outputs
- Keep ML/NLP models optional with graceful fallbacks
- Never make clinical decisions — only surface data and patterns for professionals

# Code Rules
- Python, PEP8, type hints on all public methods
- Concise — no filler code or obvious comments
- Meaningful comments where logic is non-obvious
- Dataclasses or pydantic for structured data, not raw dicts
- Explicit exception handling, no bare except:
- Prefer sklearn pipelines over ad-hoc preprocessing
- Notebooks for exploration only, scripts for production logic

# Behavior
- ALWAYS ask before running any terminal command
- State approach in 2-3 lines before writing code
- Never remove existing functionality unless explicitly told
- Summarize what changed and why after every task
- Suggest /newtask proactively when context grows large
